Class OrderAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • jade.core.Agent
      • warehouse.OrderAgent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    jade.core.TimerListener, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Runnable

    public class OrderAgent
extends jade.core.Agent

    Order agent maintains an internal HashMap with the parts contained in the order as well as a HashMap with the order it still requires. It is responsible of initiating the order fulfillment process. When assigned to a PickerAgent, the order sends a message containing the HashMap with the parts it still requires. When a shelf is chosen by the picker, a message is received containing the parts this shelf can provide, and the order updates the missing pieces list. This is once again sent to the PickerAgent so it requires a new shelf until the order is completed. Once the order is completed, it notifies the WarehouseAgent.

    Attributes:
    • partList: HashMap containing the part name and quantity originally desired.
    • missingParts: HashMap containing the part name and quantity still required.
    • orderNum: the name of the agent and order number.
    • assignedPicker: AID of the Picker to which it is assigned.
    Author:
    [DNA] Diego, Nicolas, Argentina
